0. Golden rules: 
0.1 If possible, the AI will not make a move that will directly lose the game. E.g. unlocking a red card that will give the player victory.
0.2 Conversely it will always take a move that directly wins the game. E.g. taking a red card that will give the AI victory.
0.3 All normal rules apply unless stated otherwise.
0.4 Special notes on the flowcharts take precedence over the rules below.

1. Setup changes:
1.1 Give the AI its starting progress token if applicable. (E.g. Pericles starts with Architecture) 
1.2 Remove the following progress tokens from the game (unless the AI has them): Economy, Strategy
1.3 Optional: Randomly pick the 3 guild buildings that will be used in Age 3 and reveal them.

2. Base game rules:
2.1 At the beginning of the first age the player decides who goes first.
2.2 In subsequent ages, if the AI is behind on the military track, it will choose to go first. 
2.3 The AI gets all cards for free. It still needs the required goods for wonders.
2.4 Yellow cards that let the AI buy a resource for 1 coin will give it 1 of that resource instead. If a yellow card provides more than 1 resource then treat it as "or".
2.5 The AI decides which cards to take based on its flowchart (wonders follow the same priority as in the draft).
2.6 When taking resources it will take only resources that it still needs for any of the wonders.
2.7 In the rare case that none of the actions in the flowchart applies, the AI will discard for coins.
2.8 When taking a card to discard for coins or build a wonder the inverse order of the flowchart applies.
2.9 Effects on progress tokens (except the one that it starts with) do not apply to the AI. Each progress token is worth 4 VP instead.
2.10 When taking a progress token the AI will take them from left to right. When given the chance to look at multiple tokens it will take the top one instead.

3. Pantheon rules:
3.1 When the AI takes a mythology token it will take the topmost card of the respective deck and place it face up on the cheapest free space in the pantheon.
3.2 If the AI wants to use a card in the pantheon it will check one after another, starting from the one closest to the player, whether it is eligible to play. A divinity is eligible if: printed cost + priority - smallest offering token is less than 8.
3.3 Divinity effects do not apply to the AI. Each divinity card is worth 4 VP instead.
